		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Oct 27th 7:56 PM 2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=97180486231771&num=5&page=&post=1&replyto=97269097913391"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=97269097913391></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Even with a base str of 103, I too found Bronze to be just too heavy.&nbsp;&nbsp;So at level 16 I finally started working on acquiring something else.<br><br>Jagged Bands are certainly worth the cost.  I managed to get 2 for only 50pp.  At AC5 and +3 str (each) I was eager to lay out the money.<br><br>Golden Amber Earrings do not provide any AC, but at +3 Str and only costing around 30-40pp for 2, well, easy decision.<br><br>Fine Plate Greaves were an excellent addition in many ways.  They dropped weight from the bronze while providing a point or two more AC.  To say they look better is an understatement as well.  The only drawback is the cost.  Where bronze greaves prices are now down around 10-15pp, fine plate greaves must be made and materials alone will probably take you to 200pp.<br><br>Fine Plate Boots proved to be a similar situation to the greaves.  Expect costs of over 125pp.<br><br>A Skull-shaped barbute will often go for 200pp and provides AC13 with a nice little HP boost.  If you can swing a BI crown the AC is not as good (AC 5), but the crown provides some very nice benefits that are not always obvious.  +5 str and +5 on all save categories in one item can be a godsend.  On a human it also looks much much better than the buckethead/bullethead fashions offered by bronze helms.<br><br>A straw-spun belt is AC10, but weighs in at a costly 6 stone.  However, prices seem to be dropping.  I managed to buy mine for only 30pp.<br><br>A spiked collar has proven to be the most beneficial for the cost.  These have gotten so common that 4pp seems to be the average price.  At +3 str in the neck slot with a little AC as well, the low cost astounded me.<br><br>The above are items that I bought with some hard-earned money.  From good friends and very nice people that took pity on a paladin, I managed to garner the following (which I have yet to find better):  Charred Guardian BP, Darkmail Gaunts, Silver Bracers, and Grotesque Mask.<br><br>Lanceor<br>Paladin of Mithanial Marr<br>Acceptor of 23 truths<br>Xegony Server<br><br>Perception is reality, but truth is virtuous.<br>-Mithian proverb</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=97180486231771&num=5&page=&post=1&mid=97180486231771><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 class=mform><tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>5 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class6">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
